@luke-jr upstream is now https://github.com/bitcoin-core/univalue/commit/7890db99d693572d27ade3e14268bd7236134529?\n\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blame/master/doc/developer-notes.md#L711-L712 should be updated.

Upstream is jgarzik/univalue\n\nbitcoin-core/univalue should not exist. There is no rationale for deviating from upstream, and if anything, we should be working toward removing the subtree entirely and just using the system install.
utACK faad55a.\n\n@luke-jr At least, it's a fork for now.
There's no reason for it, so NACK making it so...

Upstream has been bitcoin-core/univalue since at least https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/8807.

This PR doesn't change what the upstream branch is, so discussion of that seems off-topic for me.

ACK faad55a9a24601aac47b5e3bc44827ddb41d8f93
